dco / debugconnection         Toggles connection debugging flags

   Format:
      ;dco <switch>           Toggles a debugging flag
      ;dco                    Shows current settings for debugging flags

   Notes:
      <switch> can be any of the following:
         -q   Show invalid escape sequences messages
         -t   Show telnet option negotiations messages
         -s   Show short option negotiation messages
         -l   Telnet library writes its own logfile, telopt.log
         -d   Show messages for MSDP data sent to Status/Locator
         -x   Show messages for MXP errors
         -c   Display MXP comments
         -p   Show messages for Pueblo errors
         -u   Display Pueblo comments
         -z   Display incoming ZMP data
         -a   Display incoming ATCP data
         -g   Display incoming GMCP data
         -m   Show messages for MCP errors

      For debug messages relating to Axmud's internal processes and tasks, see
         the ';debugtoggle' command.

   User commands:
      dco / debugconnect / debugconnection
